      "span_text": "For MKL1, the majority of the peaks (68.5%, 781 out of 1140) were associated with SRF. However, the percentage for ELK4 association with SRF peaks was relatively lower (44.7%, 350 out of 783), indicating that ELK4 may have other functions independent of SRF and could have other co-regulators [CITATION_1] ."
